{"FLAIL":[{"def":"An instrument for threshing or beating grain from the ear by hand, consisting of a wooden staff or handle, at the end of which a stouter and shorter pole or club, called a swipe, is so hung as to swing freely.","pos":""},{"def":"An ancient military weapon, like the common flail, often having the striking part armed with rows of spikes, or loaded.","pos":""}],"FLAILY":[{"def":"Acting like a flail.","pos":""}],"FLAIR":[{"def":"Sense of smell; scent; fig.","pos":""}]}